Bump.

I'm looking at the source but I don't know anything about the command context stuff and therefore don't know if this is the fault of the items using the context (debugActionSet and BreakpointsView), or the command context itself.

Something is calling context.undefine() on the context mentioned "while" that context is still active (listed in the ContextManager contained in the ContextService).

The BindingManager computes a context tree from the list of active contexts by walking the parent chain ... except while this is marked as active, it has been undefined.

1) assuming that debug is undefining the context and also probably activated it, they should deactivate it before undefining it.

2) maybe we can add some code in the context manager that can hear an undefine() call on a context and wipe it from the list of active contexts.
